'''O. Henry Middle School''' is a [[middle school]] located in the [[Tarrytown, Austin, Texas|Tarrytown]] neighborhood of [[Austin, Texas]] and is a part of the [[Austin Independent School District]].  It is named after author [[O.Henry|William Sydney Porter]], whose [[pen name]] was O. Henry.  Porter lived in Austin for part of his adult life.

Notable former students at O. Henry include professional golfer [[Ben Crenshaw]] and former Major League Baseball player and manager [[Don Baylor]].  In February 1995, O. Henry was the site of a [[drive-by shooting]], in which one student was injured.

